text.section:
An applicant for a real estate appraiser trainee license shall:
submit an application to the Commission on the form that the Commission requires;
be of good character and reputation;
be at least 18 years old;
provide evidence, as required by the Commission, that the applicant has successfully completed 75 tested hours of Commission-approved real estate appraisal courses of which 15 hours shall be classroom hours in the subject of the uniform standards of professional appraisal practice; and
pay to the Commission an application fee set by the Commission.
